-- Russia Equity Movers: Gazprom, Magnitogorsk, Mechel, Surgut
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-04T16:05:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/russia-equity-movers-gazprom-magnitogorsk-novatek-surgut.html
The 30-stock Micex Index 3.6 percent
to 1,391.14 by the close in Moscow, the lowest level this year.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX) dropped 3.8 percent to 162.66 rubles,
the biggest drop since Dec. 9. UBS AG cut its price estimate on
the stock to $16 from $17.5 following the government’s approval
of doubling  Russia ’s natural-gas export monopoly’s mineral-
extraction tax for the second half of 2015.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX) fell 4.5 percent to 132.81
rubles and OAO Surgutneftegas (SNGS RX) declined 4.4 percent to
26.968 rubles. The oil arm of Russia’s gas monopoly and the
country’s fourth-largest oil producer followed crude oil lower
on worse-than-forecast U.S. economic data and Europe slowdown
concerns.  OAO Magnitogorsk Iron & Steel (MAGN RX) tumbled 4.3 percent
to 11.091 rubles, the lowest level since Oct. 5, and OAO
Novolipetsk Steel (NLMK RX) dropped 6.6 percent to 56.93 rubles.
Billionaire Victor Rashnikov’s steelmaker and Russia’s largest
steelmaker by market value retreated as metal prices fell.  OAO Mechel (MTLR)   declined 6 percent to 221 rubles, the
lowest price since July 2009. Russia’s largest producer of coal
for steelmakers will post a 12 percent revenue drop in the
fourth quarter from the third, VTB Capital analysts forecast.
The company is scheduled to post quarterly earnings on May 10.  OAO Novatek (NVTK RX) dropped 4.1 percent to 314.92 rubles
for a fourth day of declines. UBS cut its price estimate on the
stock to $150 from $186 after the government approved
quadrupling the mineral-extraction tax for independent gas
producers for the second half of 2015.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
